# datamap-explorer — desktop stack only

This repository is a **Python 3.10+ desktop application**, not a hosted React/SPA.

## Authoritative stack

- **Python 3.10+** with type hints
- **PyQt5** — main window, sidebar, directory UI, QSS styling
- **PyQtWebEngine** — `QWebEngineView` embedding the map page
- **Leaflet 1.9** (loaded in `map/index.html` from CDN) — markers, popups, pan/zoom
- **Esri World Imagery** — basemap tiles (ArcGIS URL in `map/index.html`)
- **Qt WebChannel** + `qwebchannel.js` — Python ↔ JavaScript (`ui/map_bridge.py`, `runJavaScript`)
- **CSV / JSON** — `utils/parser.py`, export in `main.py`
- **`DataPoint`** dataclass — `models/datapoint.py`

## Project layout (do not replace with a web app)

- `main.py` — entry, `AppController`, filter/sort/map/table wiring
- `ui/` — `main_window.py`, `sidebar.py`, `directory_list.py`, `datatable.py` (legacy table widget if present), `map_bridge.py`, `styles.qss`
- `map/index.html` — Leaflet map (local file loaded by WebEngine)
- `utils/` — `parser.py`, `dataset_ops.py`
- `models/` — `datapoint.py`
- `requirements-pyqt.txt` — `PyQt5`, `PyQtWebEngine`

## Do not do here

- Do **not** add or restore **React, Vite, Next.js**, npm `package.json` web builds, **Vercel** configs, or SPA entry HTML at repo root for the map UI.
- Do **not** suggest deploying this app as the primary workflow; it is run with `python main.py` after `pip install -r requirements-pyqt.txt`.

## When adding features

Extend **Python controllers**, **PyQt widgets**, **`map/index.html` JS**, and **parsers** only. Keep a single source of truth for data in the controller (`self.data` / filtered view pattern).
